dataIdInfo.idAbs: Dataset represents centerlines of major water project canals that are managed by local area government agencies or entities. This dataset does not contain major State or Federal canals. The original data were from many sources including NHD,USBR,DWR,and contained errors in the attributes and locations. These errors were rectified by Jeff Galef of DWR Delta Levees Special Investigations Branch, using 2005 and 2006 NAIP imagery and Central Valley Aerials Express. These updates were as of 2009. Conflicts between this original data source and any new linework added was resolved using NAIP imagery from 2012. Digitizing was done at approximately 1:9000 scale. Many unnamed canals were identified using USGS topo maps and ESRI Street Map. Additional canal features were added in November 2017 which were inadvertently not included in the initial dataset. The associated data are considered DWR enterprise GIS data, which meet all appropriate requirements of the DWR GIS Spatial Data Standards. DWR makes no warranties or guarantees, either expressed or implied, as to the completeness, accuracy or correctness of the data, nor accepts or assumes any liability arising from or for any incorrect, incomplete or misleading subject data. The official DWR GIS steward for this data set is Jane Schafer-Kramer, who may be contacted at 916-653-4441, or at jane.schafer-kramer@water.ca.gov. Comments, problems, improvements, updates, or suggestions should be forwarded to the official GIS steward as available and appropriate.
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
General inventory and mapping of secondary canal features within the water delivery system throughout the state of California. This data is primarily suited for regional or statewide mapping. Should not be used for precise engineering or survey purposes. Data does not include Federal or State owned or operated canals.
The associated data are considered DWR enterprise GIS data, which meet all appropriate requirements of the DWR Spatial Data Standards, specifically the DWR Spatial Data Standard version 3.1, dated September 11, 2019. DWR makes no warranties or guarantees — either expressed or implied — as to the completeness, accuracy, or correctness of the data. DWR neither accepts nor assumes liability arising from or for any incorrect, incomplete, or misleading subject data. The official DWR GIS steward for this data set is Jane Schafer-Kramer, who may be contacted at 916-653-4441, or at jane.schafer-kramer@water.ca.gov. Comments, problems, improvements, updates, or suggestions should be forwarded to the official GIS steward as available and appropriate.

report.measDesc: 2014 NAIP 4-band imagery was used to validate location of canals. NAIP imagery was used as a reference to adjust the Canals and Aqueducts dataset. KNown error for this dataset is 6 meters horizontal accuracy. The datasets were viewed and adjusted at a scale of 1:9,000. ACE/ALE method was used to determine positional accuracy.

NAIP 2014 imagery was used as a reference dataset. PAAT tool ALE/ACE method was used to determine absolute and relative error at 95% confidence level. A total of 27 observations resulted in a circular error of 456 meters. Calculation method NGA Standard.

Positional accuracy: tested to 456 meters horizontal accuracy at 95% confidence level using Positional accuracy assessment Method 6. NAIP 2014 imagery used as reference having a known error of 6 meters horizontal positional accuracy.

Locational Quality: Determined to be no better than 456 meters horizontal. This report is not being made by a licensed land surveyor, and is not analogous to a positional accuracy statement as stipulated in the California Public Resources Code.
report.evalMethDesc: Positional accuracy Assessment Method 6 was used. ACE/ALE method used in positional accuracy tool, Data Reviewer extension. ACE/ALE method was used and Circular error resulted in 456 meters horizontal accuracy from reference dataset, NAIP 2014 imagery.
